```tactics
def construction (T : FTheory L) (hT : χ ➝ ξ ∉ T.theorem) : ℕ → Set (Formula ℕ)
  | 0 => { δ | χ ➝ δ ∈ T.theorem }
  | i + 1 =>
    match (decode i) with
    | some δ =>
      letI T' := construction T hT i
      if ∀ Γ : Finset (Formula _), ↑Γ ⊆ T' → Γ.conj ⋏ δ ➝ ξ ∉ T.theorem then insert δ T'
      else T'
    | none => construction T hT i
```

This defines the recursive construction of the set.

```tactics
def construction_omega (T : FTheory L) (hT : χ ➝ ξ ∉ T.theorem) : Set (Formula ℕ) := ⋃ i, construction T hT i
```

This defines the omega construction as the union of the recursive constructions.

```tactics
lemma subset_construction_succ : construction T hT i ⊆ construction T hT (i + 1) := by
  dsimp [construction];
  split;
  . split <;> tauto;
  . tauto;
```

This lemma shows that each construction is a subset of the next.

```tactics
lemma subset_construction_add : construction T hT i ⊆ construction T hT (i + j) := by
  induction j with
  | zero => simp;
  | succ j ih =>
    trans construction T hT (i + j);
    . apply ih;
    . apply subset_construction_succ;
```

This lemma shows that the construction is monotone with respect to addition.

```tactics
lemma monotone_construction (hij : i ≤ j) : construction T hT i ⊆ construction T hT j := by
  obtain ⟨k, rfl⟩ := le_iff_exists_add.mp hij;
  apply subset_construction_add;
```

This lemma shows that the construction is monotone with respect to the less than or equal relation.

