lemma construction_omega_not_mem_csq : ξ ∉ construction_omega T hT := by
  simp only [construction_omega, Set.mem_iUnion, not_exists];
  intro i;
  induction i with
  | zero => simpa [construction];
  | succ i ih =>
    contrapose! ih;
    dsimp [construction] at ih;
    split at ih;
    . split_ifs at ih with h;
      . rename_i δ hδ;
        have := h ∅ (by tauto);
        contrapose! this;
        have : ξ = δ := by grind;
        subst this;
        apply T.mem_of_provable;
        simp;
      . assumption;
    . assumption;
```

This lemma shows that `ξ` is not in the omega set. The proof is by contradiction. If `ξ` were in the omega set, then there exists `i` such that `ξ ∈ construction T hT i`. This would mean `T` proves `χ → ξ`, which would imply `ξ ∈ T`. But `hT` says `χ → ξ ∉ T`. This is a contradiction.

